<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    SyncingKeys SDK privacy manifest
    ================================
    Audited 2026-05-12. The SDK does NOT use any of Apple's "required reason
    APIs" — see https://developer.apple.com/documentation/bundleresources/privacy_manifest_files/describing_use_of_required_reason_api
    for the canonical list. Concretely:

      • Security.framework (SecItemAdd/Get/Update/Delete, SecKeyXxx) — not on
        the required-reason list.
      • LocalAuthentication.framework (LAContext, BiometricPrompt) — not on
        the list.
      • Foundation.FileManager.ubiquityIdentityToken — not on the list (only
        the file-attributes APIs around modification/access time are
        required-reason-gated).
      • UIDevice.current.systemVersion — not on the list.

    No collected data types are declared because the SDK only reads / writes
    opaque encrypted envelopes that it generates locally; it never observes
    or transmits user-identifying or device-identifying data on the wire.

    Update this comment block whenever you audit. The file itself stays
    minimal (empty arrays) because that is what App Store reviewers expect
    for a no-collection SDK.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>NSPrivacyTrackingDomains</key>
	<array/>
	<key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>
	<array/>
	<key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes</key>
	<array/>
	<key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>
	<false/>
</dict>
</plist>
